      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="insert_link" data-step-uuid="FDD6DFCB-E9F2-491C-9511-425E1DB8F708">
    <h2 id="insert_link" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Insert Link</h2>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <a href="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/004/057/146/original/e45fbdbf-8ee1-4941-b549-4db3d05cf312.png" class="screensteps-image-zoom" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">
        <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/004/057/146/medium/e45fbdbf-8ee1-4941-b549-4db3d05cf312.png" srcset="" alt="Insert Link" height="363" width="855">
      </a>
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_FAF9DD40-221C-0135-A9C8-22000BC102FE" class="text-block-content">
    <p>In the Rich Content Editor, place your cursor where you want to insert the link. You can <a href="/t5/Instructor-Guide/How-do-I-create-hyperlinks-to-course-or-group-content-in-the/ta-p/954" target="_blank">add links to course or group content</a>. The name of the page will appear in the Rich Content Editor and flash yellow. Then the name will turn blue, indicating it is a link.</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>

